.SH NAME
MediaQueryList.matches \- MediaQueryList: matches property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]matches\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]MediaQueryList\f[R] interface is a boolean value that returns
\f[CR]true\f[R] if the \f[CR]document\f[R] currently matches the media
query list, or \f[CR]false\f[R] if not.
.PP
You can be notified when the value of \f[CR]matches\f[R] changes by
watching for the \f[CR]change\f[R] event to be fired at the
\f[CR]MediaQueryList\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A boolean value that is \f[CR]true\f[R] if the \f[CR]document\f[R]
currently matches the media query list; otherwise, it\[cq]s
\f[CR]false\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
This example detects viewport orientation changes by creating a media
query using the \f[CR]orientation\f[R] media feature:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] mql = window.matchMedia(\[dq](orientation:landscape)\[dq]);
mql.addEventListener(\[dq]change\[dq], (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]if\f[R] (event.matches) {
    console.log(\[dq]Now in landscape orientation\[dq]);
  } \f[B]else\f[R] {
    console.log(\[dq]Now in portrait orientation\[dq]);
  }
});
.EE
